    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-09-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-09-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="127"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d127">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Adams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1096.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-09-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 20, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 18th of August, No. 760, has
                    been received, together with a copy of correspondence which has recently taken
                    place between yourself and Earl Russell on subjects connected with the African
                    slave trade.</p>
                <p>I will at once call on the United States consul general at Havana for such
                    information as he may be able to give concerning the supposed new steam slaver
                    mentioned by Earl Russell.</p>
                <p>The Secretary of the Navy has under consideration the inquiry of his lordship
                    concerning our present ability to send out cruisers according to the treaty
                    stipulation for the special purpose of suppressing the trade in slaves. I will
                    advise you promptly of the decision of the government, when made.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
